A brief explanation of the difference between localhost, 0.0.0.0, and the Tailscale address used in a client URL:
localhost means the same machine only.
0.0.0.0 means the server listens on all network interfaces.
The Tailscale address like 100.x.y.z is the private client URL your laptop uses to reach the class server over Tailscale.

