A brief written summary of the three design decisions:
Full proxy API: the backend owns SQLite and all Kepler calls, while the CLI stays focused on user-friendly terminal output.
Separate server command: the backend runs as its own bun run server process instead of being hidden inside the CLI.
Resource-shaped REST routes: the backend exposes real resources like /registration, /modules, /inventory, /catalog/blueprints, and /solar/irradiance instead of mirroring Commander commands.

A brief written summary of which responsibilities now belong to the CLI and which belong to the Hono backend:
CLI responsibilities: argument parsing, friendly messages, table formatting, and command-level validation.
Hono backend responsibilities: SQLite persistence, registration state, module/inventory state, and Kepler proxy calls.

A brief note explaining why the logs are sanitized:
They only print route, method, status, and a short summary.
They do not print bearer tokens, API tokens, or full request/response bodies.

